Interface ITaskContext


  • public interface ITaskContext
    Represents the concept of a task context which can be switched into and out of using class TaskContext.

      <T> T getTaskSpecific(Class<T> clazz)

    • Method Detail

      • getTaskSpecific

        <T> T getTaskSpecific(Class<T> clazz)
        Provides access to a task's task specifics, a map of Class-index objects.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The compile-time type of the object to query.
        Parameters:
        clazz - The Class that serves as a key for the task specific.
        Returns:
        An object of type T or null if none was registered under the given key.
